data.title: Venkatesh
data.meta_description: Daggubati Venkatesh (born 13 December 1960), known mononymously as Venkatesh, is an Indian film actor known for his works predominantly in Telugu cinema. Rana Daggubati (nephew) (brother's son) Naga Chaitanya (nephew) (sister's son) Akkineni Nagarjuna (former brother-in-law)
data.text: Pavitra Bandham Anokha Bandhan Vijay Ganessh Divekar 2014 Remade in Hindi as Hum Aapke Dil Mein Rehte Hain (1999) and in Tamil as Priyamaanavale (2000) (Hindi dub titled Dil Ki Baat) with Venkatesh's role reprised by Anil Kapoor and Vijay respectively. Nuvvu Naaku Nachav Meri Haan Teri Naa Hindi Venkateswarlu "Venky" Sachin Gole 2021 Remade in Tamil as Vaseegara (2003) (Hindi dub titled Ek Aur Loafer) with Venkatesh's role reprised by Vijay. Gemeni Aaj Ka Shoorveer Hindi Gemeni Ganessh Divekar 2008 Remake of Tamil film Gemini (2002) (Hindi dub titled Angaar: The Deadly One). 2006 Lakshmi Meri Taaqat Hindi Lakshmi Narayana "Lakshmi" (Lakshmi Narasimha in Hindi version and Surya Narasimha "Surya" in Hindustani version) Ganessh Divekar 2007 2015 Gopala Gopala Hindi Kanneganti Gopal Rao (Haridas Gopal Rao in Hindi version) Chetanya Adib 2018 Remake of Hindi film OMG - Oh My God (2012).
